cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI 

This paper focuses on investigating the generalizability of EEG-based cognitive load estimation across different visualizations for a given analytic task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as deep convolutional neural networks and proximal support vector machines, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing visualizations, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
